title: Mighty Safari Warthog Squeaky Plush Dog Toy
descriptions:
["This Mighty Safari Warthog is the paw-fect toy for dogs who like to play a little “ruff”. This plush toy is reinforced with multiple layers of durable materials and has several layers of stitching that’s flipped inside for added strength. It's great for fetching and tugging and it makes an excellent companion to accompany your pup during a game of toss and catch. To really get your pup excited, give his new friend a squeeze to activate the squeaker that’s sewn inside a pocket for added safety! Once your long day of play is done, simply place your BFF’s new pal in the washing machine for easy cleaning.", '

                        See all items by Mighty
']
key_benefits: ["This plush is not only soft to the touch, but it's durable too!", 'Multiple layers of materials and several rows of stitching are used to help extend the life of the toy.', 'Machine washable for easy, hassle-free cleaning.', 'Contains a squeaker that’s sewn inside a safety pocket to help protect your pup in case he rips his new toy open.', 'This tough toy is paw-fect for tugging, tossing, catching and fetching!']
reviews: [Our Pyrenees’s puppy is an aggressive chewer! Most regular stuffed toys don’t last more than a week for her. This toy is firm and packed full of stuffing. It took her almost 3 months to disassemble! Do note...the bizarre amount of stuffing in this toy is deceiving. Your home will look like a winter wonderland when your dog has taken apart this toy, This isn’t the toughest toy, but it’s adorable! Just be careful if your dog tends to eat non-edible things- the hair on this little warthog come off easily. This toy is pretty firm and not squishy like other plush toys- making it pretty tough!, When I first received this toy I was impressed with how sturdy it seemed but after a tug battle my dogs broke it open and de-stuffed it. On the bright side..the stuffing was easier to clean up than other stuffed toys.]

title: Tuffy's Togo Toucan Plush Dog Toy
descriptions:
['Move over Sam and get a load of Togo! This "Tuff" tropical tweeter makes a colorful companion for your canine.', 'Please Note: Togo does not squeak!', "The Tuffy's Series Toys are designed to be play toys and not chew toys. Every dog plays differently and, since not all toys are created equal, it’s always best to keep a close watch on your pup in case things get ruff. Supervised play will help toys last longer and most importantly keep your pal safe. No dog toy is truly indestructible, so always remove the toy from playtime if pieces begin to break off.", "

                        See all items by Tuffy's
"]
key_benefits: ['Made with three layers that are bonded and sewn together to make one "Tuff" Layer. Most toys have just one seam to hold the toy together, Tuffy\'s has 7. Webbing is sewn around the edges of the toy and then the edges are sewn together to make each toy extra Tuff. Each toy is then stuffed with safe, non-toxic fiber and has soft edges that are safe on gums', 'Contains no squeakers', 'Floats in water and is machine washable (air dry)', 'Tuff scale: 8 out of 10', 'Size is ideal for medium to large dogs']
reviews: [This toucan is quite large and so far has held up really well. We have a strong chewer and another dog who's afraid of high-pitched noises so the lack of squeaker was a big selling point., My Great Dane loves holding his bird and throwing it up in the air. It’s tough and durable. It’s been several months and no holes., Do not buy if your dog is a heavy chewer it is quite durable strong fabric and cool chew toy but my boxer is a very ruff and oversized due to him being mixed with American bull dog very aggressive with his toys so do not buy if your pet is same way toy was destroyed in few hours, The Tuffy's Toucan can hold up to your chewer. Plus, it's a good size for the price point. My dog has ruined all his toys within the five minutes. This one is still holding strong after one month. Tuffy's Dog Toys are the only ones I will now buy., I was SO surprised that this toy has lasted this long before being opened by my nephews dog - she's a beautiful & sweet American Staffordshire Terrier Pit Bull & she loves to nibble on the seams of her toys (hahaha!) when she's not retrieving them... we received this at the beginning of May & she opened the belly seams yesterday (it lasted 3 whole months!!)...hahaha! Toys are normally destroyed & gutted within the first hour of receiving them..., Did not think it was good quality We have a Lab puppies and the toy did not last more then one hour. Was very disappointed!, When I ordered I thought there was only one size. I got the large toucan and my dog won't play with it at all. I thought I was getting the smaller one. I'm disappointed., I have a 10 month Doberman and she's shredded every toy I've given her except this one. It's 100% intact. Not a single stitch is broken. I've paid equal amount for other toys that didn't last until nightfall the same day., This Tuffys toy didn't make it 15 min with my dog before the stuffing was all over the floor. I would expect a little better product with a name like Tuffys. I wouldn't recommend buying this toy at all, even for the littlest of dogs. My pug even got the stuffing out in a matter of minutes. Poorly made product., I have great luck with all the Tuffy brand toys. So far the Toucan toy is also holding up well for my 5 month old Doberman and the adult Dobermans as well.]

title: Tuffy's Junior Bowmerang Squeaky Plush Dog Toy
descriptions:
['Tuffy's Junior Bow-merang Dog Toy is ideal for dogs training for Flyball or who just like to whip their toys back and forth. It’s made with three layers of safe, non-toxic fibers: soft fleece, industrial grade luggage material, and plastic coating. All three are fused and sewn together to make one ultra "tuff" layer, ensuring this toy is just as durable as it is fun. It also has a protective pouch around its squeaker as an added safety measure in the event that your destroyer gets to the core. This toy is great for indoor use because of its soft exterior, perfect for outdoor use because it floats in water, and easy to clean because it’s machine washable.', "The Tuffy's Series Toys are designed to be play toys and not chew toys. Every dog plays differently and, since not all toys are created equal, it’s always best to keep a close watch on your pup in case things get ruff. Supervised play will help toys last longer and most importantly keep your pal safe. No dog toy is truly indestructible, so always remove the toy from playtime if pieces begin to break off.", "

                        See all items by Tuffy's
"]
key_benefits: ['Assembled with multiple seams and webbing to make this toy a worthy opponent for most moderate chewers.', 'Made with 3 uniquely fused layers for added durability during play.', 'Squeaker is sewn into a pouch for safe-keeping, allowing an extra layer of protection.', 'Floats in water for added fun and machine washable for easy cleaning.', 'Rates a cool #8 on Tuffy\'s own "Tuff Scale."']
reviews: [Our pup has difficulty in not destroying a toy immediately! This one lasted much longer than the others. All the Tuffy's do!!!, My dog had this thing chewed open in about 10 minutes. Was hoping that this would last a little bit. Have a hard time finding toys she doesn’t destroy in less than a couple hours and reading the reviews I thought this would last a while. Another one bites the dust., My dog really enjoys this toy because it's good for throwing like a frisbee or tug of war or just chew time. However, when we first received this product 1 of the 3 squeakers worked well, 1 of the 3 had a slight squeak if you pressed hard enough, and the last squeaker did not work at all! Before my dog had even taken one bite into it., We have two miniature dachshunds that love to chew and have been difficult to buy toys for since they would destroy them in 5 minutes to maybe a few days if we were lucky. Having a good variety of things for them to chew has never kept them from destroying their toys and they love toys like most dachshunds seem to. This is the first brand we have found that endures our "girls" playing habits. The first boomerang lasted about 4-5 months and really could have been scissor trimmed on the edges and still used. We have another product by them that we purchased about the same time that is still doing great. We hope they increase their product line especially for smaller dogs. We have purchased three, this Tuffy Jr is great on toughness, easy to play tug o war with smaller dogs, My beagle. Had the squeakers torn out of this in a half hour. I was surprised because he has other tuffy toys that lasted much longer .]

reviews: [Would not recommend dog had tore up in less than 10 minutes. reviews: [This is the best brand of stuffed toys I have found for my dog. He is a 3 year old Shepherd. He chews the limbs from most stuffed toys in 1 hour. reviews: [The dogs all love this toy. There is enough stuffing and a squeaker to make it interesting, but no one needed to rip it apart. reviews: [This is my dog's favorite toy! reviews: [I’ve purchased a few different Tuffy toys for my dog and he has loved all of them. This one is hilarious because it’s almost as big as my 35 lb. cattle dog but he still tries to thrash it like the rest of his smaller toys. He can’t quite figure out how to carry it up the stairs yet and it’s so funny to watch. It’s a little dense and heavy, which is why I gave it 4 stars rather than 5., Torn apart in literally minutes. These toys usually last a while this one is garbage., I usually love this company and brand but my red lab tore a huge hole in this sheep sadly within 1-2 days so for the price and usual quality of these toys I expected it to last way longer. Though it is bigger in person than I imagined, This item is too large, even for a large german shepherd., So I thought I bought the junior size of this, but when it arrived it was the size of my dogs. Both Jack Russells were thrilled with my mistake and have been happy with our newest household edition. After dragging Sherman around by his butt for the better part of the day, my one jack finally hoisted him over the couch and into his den aka our bay window. Sherman then spent several days snuggled up in the sunny spot until my other jack pulled him down and began a wrestling match quite unlike any other. His favorite move is to grab Sherman by the ear and in a WWE style, flip him over his back and onto the ground. I am impressed by the fact the saber-toothed-terriers haven't been able to open, My 6mo old lab loves this! Was looking for a new toy that he wouldn't destroy right away, and so far he hasn't. It's great!, Lizzy loves her lamb. She chews on it. She tosses it. But best of all it’s still whole. She has not destroyed the lamb! Yeah lamb, It’s a little bit heavy but it’s really nice my dog has been playing with it for weeks and it has not ripped that’s unsual for my dog he destroys everything, Hi, I bought this because of the reviews stating how indestructible it is. Within minutes my corgi ripped off and ingested the ears. The started tearing off its face and tail. It appears only the feet are reinforced. It’s also HUGE, it’s basically the size of my corgi - that may be my fault for not checking dimensions. But I do not recommend this for any chewy dogs., Sheena loved this sheep. She shook him and dragged him around for two days. Then she chewed off his ears. After that she found a weak spot in the leg and ripped him open. Too much money spent regretfully.]

reviews: [I HAVE TWO LARGE TUFF CHEWERS. A GERMAN SHEPARD PUPPY UNDER 6 MONTHS WHO IS TEETHING AND A POINTER THAT 2 YEARS AND DESTROYS ALL IN HER PATH. I DIDN'T HAVE MUCH HOPE IN THIS TOY LASTING THE HOUR BETWEEN THE TWO OF THEM BUT TO MY SURPRISE IT'S HOLDING UP STRONG. WE ARE UP TO TWO WEEKS NOW OF TUFF CHEWS AND ROUGH PLAY AND THIS TOY DOESN'T EVEN SHOW WEAR. IT'S ALSO A VERY LARGE SIZE SO BOTH MY PUPS CAN PLAY WITH IT AS ONCE WHICH IS AN ADDED BONUS. LIKE I RECOMMEND WITH ANY TOY REVIEW I DO NOT RECOMMEND UNSUPERVISED PLAY, AS PET OWNERS KNOW DOGS CAN DESTROY ANYTHING IF GIVEN AMPLE TIME TO DO SO AND IT CAN BECOME A HAZARD. OVERALL FANTASTIC TOY., Jojo is a little intimidated by the giraffe at first . But he has sunk his teeth into it and He put the giraffe in its place it will never be the same, Bought for my dog Charlotte. Its very well made and I know it will take a while for her to even make a dent. I wish it had a squeaker though. She gets bored of it faster than other toys. Thats my one problem with it., Tyler is a 2 1/2 year old gigantic 90lb collie that absolutely LOVES this Tuffy giraffe toy. He either has this or one the large dinosaur Tuffy toys. He brings it everywhere and even sleeps on it. He is NOT some dainty dog, either. He has eaten / destroyed everything else including wood furniture / the couch / clothes / etc. He occasionally chews on it but I think he likes that it is just SO LARGE. All my dogs are rescues and are spoiled rotten and the Tuffy toys always last the longest. There isn't a brand I have not bought for our canine crew, but the huge Tuffy's are by far Tyler's favorite. I very rarely think so highly of something, but this toy definitely gets five paws up. , This is the only toy that my pit bull has not been able to rip apart. I rate it 10/10 for tuff-ness! It’s expensive, but has lasted a looong time., Large tear after one afternoon of light play. Surgery was performed so will see how it holds up., I bought this toy for Greta a beautiful golden retriever who loves toys. She lives in the sw of Virginia where her owners Bruce and Jacky have about 15 acres and a pond. The Giraffe is suppose to float and be easy to clean. So far Greta has been enjoying her toy outside., Cute, but there are too many vulnerabilities to this product. The horns and ears, for example, were among the first to go. I wish cuteness had been sacrificed more for durability.]

descriptions:

reviews: [We love West Paw products and our dog Lucy has many of them. They are sturdy, washable and Lucy loves playing with them. When the CHEWY box arrived with the Tango toy, Lucy was clearly very excited and wanted to play with it right away. Unfortunately a few moments after she started playing with it the eyes were gone. In less that an hour the center squeaker and the padding around it were out of the toy and on her bed. This poses a choking problem. This was a cute toy, but not up to West Paw standards., My dogs ripped this apart in 2 days. I bought it because the brand has a reputation of being indestructable, My puppy loved this toy. However, the cute eyes came off within an hour. Luckily, I found them and my puppy didn't swallow them. It was still a great toy. The stitching threads were gradually pulled loose until the stuffing was reached. This toy lasted about 1.5 weeks. Way too expensive for that short of a life., Cute toy - but not suitable for an aggressive chewer like out Golden Retriever. Lasted one hour before being ripped to shreds., I am always pleased with West Paw dog toys. My mini- Schnauzer has all of them now and loves each and every one of them!, After having great luck with the green salsa monster I decided to try a different style. But this toy was ripped apart within days of getting it. Not sure if it was a bad batch or if it is not built as sturdy. Either way, I will not get this toy again. The salsa monster, after a year of being chewed, is mostly still intact (as can be seen in the photo)., The toy is very soft and nicely made, but our dog didn't show any interest in the toy :( he is picky, I wouldn't blame the toy., This toy appeared so cute looking at the picture. For the price charged, I expected way more. It is no more than 13 inches in length and the eyes are tiny. There is a squeaker in the body and in only one hand. The picture shown is deceiving. Extremely overpriced for the quality., I purchased a few of these West Paw dog toys because they were made in the USA. When I received them I found that they were shabbily made. Eyes were pompoms easily pulled off and the tango dog toy looked like parts were glued on. Very disappointed., My 72 lb pitty destroys toys with such joy I almost hate to deny him the privilege. He really loves tug of war, too, and gets pretty excited so toys that put some distance between hands and teeth are good. Although he didn't play with it terribly frequently ( once or twice a week), he had a few really good play sessions and it lasted a record 3 weeks! I'd be willing to bet this would mean a super long lasting toy for most dogs. Only one complaint, the fur comes off the toy pretty easily and is pretty hard to clean up.]

reviews: [This is the only toy my Dobermans have not destroyed in a matter of minutes!!!, I have three dogs and one is a massive chewer, it's to the point where you have to keep him crated at night and when you're not home or he will go through the house finding anything to chew up while bypassing his bones. The only problem I seen with the ring is that only one squeaker works but that's okay, he doesn't mind that it doesn't really squeak., This is much larger than what appears in the picture which is better for my Diesel. He loves sticking his head through the hole to play with his other Tuffy toys. He quickly chewed and pulled at the edges which are now frayed and have to be regular trimmed so he doesn't swallow any threads. It is only a matter of time before he rips through it but so far it has withstood his fury., My 11 month old Lab loved it. Unfortunately, he started chewing around the edges. After about a week he managed to tear a hole in the material and started pulling out the stuffing. Was really hoping this would last, Within 30 min of unpackaging this toy for my Lab Harper, the item was destroyed. In fairness to the brand Tuffy, no brand or toy seems to withstand the relentless chewing of my dog., Not all the squeakers squeak. Maybe one does well, one is very muted and the rest don't squeak. Unfortunately my dog is just not interested. It is tough for those with less picky dogs in need of a really tough toy., At 148 pounds he loves to toss this around and chew until he tires out! Holds up great. I have been using Tuffy products for 10 plus years., Toy was very tuff and just what they needed. They loved their present when they opened it., My cane corso loves it! reviews: [My nearly year old PekiChi is obsessed with Unicorns. For whatever reason (I think it's the shiny horn) he is drawn to unicorns and has been since first picking out a toy at the pet store at a little over two months when he chose a rainbow unicorn. I have heard a fair share of unfunny jokes from amateur "comedians", whose excuse for wit would make the ouvre of Adam Sandler look like Oscar Wilde's in comparison, about my dog's favorite animal and could frankly care less. I don't need an XX-TREME SUPER CHEWER DINOSKULL toy to validate my dog or me, but I LOVE that Fringe made a "boy" llamacorn. My dog is blisfully unaware of the social politics however, and from what I can assess loves four , My 16-lb., 8-1/2 year old maltese mix is usually not that obsessed with toys. Mostly she plays with a stuffed critter for about 5 minutes, and then forgets about it. She got this 6 weeks ago and is obsessed! She carries it everywhere, even managing with some effort to take it with her up and down the stairs when she goes to bed. It has the loudest, strongest squeaker... still going strong after 6 weeks (and that part usually only lasts a couple of days at best). Initially, I bought this despite thinking it was too pretty to last, so I'm very pleasantly surprised. I will definitely be buying more from this toy line. Just brought home a rescued shih tzu and he's definitely got his eye on it, but]

reviews: [This ( and some of its friends) were bought for my seven-month-old, 3 lb chihuahua... HE LOVES THEM... The little monkey has been in a tug of wars with them all playing together. I check it after each of these events and other than the 'new' look fading away into the look of a much-loved toy, it's as sturdy as it was when new. I now have different, My tiny mutt loves this toy. It’s durable so it will last!, This is a durable little toy for a tiny dog. It’s just the right size. My little girl loved playing with the monkey... I would recommend it., The squeaker was broken the first day but it remains her favorite toy., Perfect little toy for my baby yorkie! She can actually get her tiny mouth around it! Great toy., This is my chihuahua's favorite toy and I was SO happy to find them on chewy since they were no longer in the store!! Squeaker has lasted over 9 months., Within three minutes of giving my English Pointer this toy, he had three out of four limbs ripped off. Two minutes after that, the whole thing was ripped open, fluff everywhere and I had to take it away. This is not a durable toy and hardly worth the money., We bought four of these small monkeys for our Grand-dog, a 100 lb German Rottweiler. He loves to carry them around and doesn't really destroy them. However, over time the ears, arms and tail seem to come off. This is his favorite toy., Toy is cute and my pup likes it, but the squeaker was very hard to squeeze and didn't work well when I could manage it. My dog was never able to squeeze hard enough., We love the toys made by Smart Pet Love that are "Tender Tuff" they hold up so well!]

reviews: [We have a Great Dane who is fairly gentle with her toys. I received this toy from Chewy in the mail about five minutes ago, and the squeaker stopped squeaking about two minutes ago. Our doggie probably got about 10 squeaks out of it before it broke. The only reason I give it one star is because the toy *looks* fairly durable and don’t think she will rip it open any time soon. However, this is useless to her without the squeaker. So I pretty much just threw away around $15., we have a corgi mix who is a hard chewer, most toys last at most 45 min. This toy lasted 2 days with constant squeeking and chewing. He loved it and the squeaker was not annoying, low pitch, someone put lot of effort into maaking this, I am going to order at least one more., this toy is rated to be strong and tuff...I found that my dog was able to chew it to pieces in a matter of 15 mins...not recommended for strong chewers, I have 2 pit bull mixes and they destroy every toy I’ve given them, not this one though! We’ve had it for almost a month now and no rips! The squeaker did die after a couple days because one of my dogs ran around the house squeaking it nonstop for those days but they still love to play tug with it and fetch! I did purchase another toy from the same brand ( the yellow Dino one ) and it didn’t do nearly as well and ripped maybe 2 weeks after they got it. But overall very good the first toy that’s held up!, This pterosaur was way too tender, not enough tough. My dog loved it so much that she had opened the seams within ten minutes. It was super cute, though!, Cute toy but it didn’t stand a chance with my Great Pyrenees. He had it ripped open in no time. Wish someone would make a chew toy tough enough for big dogs. Sadly most of them end up in the trash in a very short amount of time., This is the only toy we have ever had that has lasted! 2 months in and it is abused daily!, Great toy. I've had this a couple months and it's still going strong, but my boy isn't a huge chewer. But I'll buy another one once this one is destroyed., This toy is durable and very high quality. My puppy loves it - he often runs around the house with it in his mouth, looking full of pride!, My dog got through the tail to remove the squeaker pretty quickly. The rest is still in pretty good shape and he is still enjoying it.]

reviews: [My young Standard Schnauzer, who can chew through anything!, LOVES his chicken! reviews: [In my opinion, this toy is too expensive. There are lots of really durable toys out there for less money...I got this because I got it for the wholesale price (about 40% less) because I work at a pet daycare/lodging place. My 7-month old doberman (who's great at destroying his favorite toys) loved it, but so did an adult golden retriever, who got ahold of it and had it in pieces within SECONDS. I was shocked because I've heard so much about how durable these toys are. I got another one (The Lincoln, which is the same but with slightly different arm lengths) and my puppy still loves it, and it's still holding up great. Not sure if the first one was defective somehow, or if that golden retriever, We have a Rottweiler puppy who has always been big for her age. She loves playing plush toys but equally loves destroying them. She typically chews off stuffed animals paws first which is one of the things that make these great! This toy is an MVP! We've had it for about 5 months now and he is longest living plush toy in our pup has had! We are buying different kinds of these because we know they'll last!, This toy is as tough as advertised. My dog loves playing with plush toys but usually destroys them in a day. We’ve had “Rowdy” for 3 weeks now and he’s still in one piece! We play tug of war with him and he has still survived. If you have a chewer, this is the toy for your pup!, This is the ONLY soft toy that has survived in our house. Our dog really loves pulling all the stuffing out of toys, but this one hasn't ripped yet. It's been through the wash a lot, which is nice because it sometimes spends the afternoon outside in the rain. The fur is a little matted from the dryer, but we've had it for about 6 months and not a single rip., Handmade in Bozeman, Montana and my dog loves these Rowdies. Every holiday I get him a new one but they hold up so well he has quite a collection. He’s a border collie and can destroy a normal stuffed toy in minutes but the rowdies are sturdy. Currently deciding on his new one for Xmas. Highly recommend., I got TWO of these for my labs.. they love the plastic west paw toys. These soft ones are pretty pricey and not worth the money.. had them shredded in days even though they claim for tougher chewers, This $35 toy came was the recommendation of a Chewy representative after previous toys had been destroyed. I was very hesitant because of the price, but I gave it a whirl with high hopes. In the first five minutes, she had pulled large tufts of hair all over the floor, but a cursory inspection looked like it hadn't succeeded in tearing any holes or seams. Another five minutes and I saw the flash of white. Ten minutes to destruction. Don't bother if you have a chewer., My 11 month old puppy chews up EVERY toy and bed we’ve tried, except for Jefferson. He’s had it several months and loves it. He chews on the rubber ends and pulls at the “hair”, but it’s survived. I cannot believe my power chewer hasn’t destroyed it. He plays with it every day. It has even survived daily games of tug of war. We were so please that we ordered a different West Paw rowdie, Custer. Love it too., Within 15 minuets our Dane puppy had all the rubber arm ends chewed off. The body held up fairly well. However, after a short Sesson of play it turns into a wet and nasty spit mop.]

reviews: [I have two large terriers and this toy is perfect for them to grasp when playing each other. Also, super tough material. reviews: [Just take one look at this toy, and you have to get it. This Mighty toy hold up great to tons of rough play between us and our dog. AND when the neighbor's dog gets involved, one should worry about the cow's safety, but he held up great to tug of war! (Poor cow) He is durable & strong, and we couldn't be happier with this toy., Within 3 days i am throwing away the cow and all its fluff. I know i cant expect chew proof but this toy is too expensive for it to last 3 days., Wow. The fact that this was delivered 32 minutes ago and I've spent the last 18 picking up stuffing should say it all. But just in case that doesn't: They claim this is the "paw-fect toys for dogs who like to play a little “ruff”". No, not even close. They claim "This plush toy is reinforced with multiple layers of durable materials" but having just gotten a really good look at the inside of this toy and the "layers", I can assure you there are no layers (see picture). Same with the claim "several layers of stitching that’s flipped inside for added strength". It's a stitch similar to what you would see on a quilt, but there aren't several layers of these stitches. The only reinforced, I was very disappointed to find a pile a fluff on my couch no more than 5 minutes after I took this thing out of the box. Both arms were half ripped off. My dog will destroy these types of toys but it usually takes a few days at least. Given the price point and the fact that the description advertises it as a tug toy, I was expecting something much more durable. I will not be buying another one of these., My dogs pretty good at taking apart her toys in a short time. But this was a new record for her. And to me the advertisement was to convince that this was durable. I won’t be buying this brand again.]

reviews: [We gave this to our Doberman pup Christmas eve...he was under supervision, but that long skinny nose is the weak spot . The body is super tough! Sadly we had to throw is away first night, as there was white stuffing...bad., My dog ripped this open in the first day, and started unstuffing it., My 40 pound schnoodle ripped through this guy within a day, This is the only Tuffy's toy that didn't last with my dog. Chloe is an 80 lb black lab chewing machine.The tail was gone in about an hour. Luckily I found it about 3 days later in the back yard. No surgery , yeah. The shell came off in the next couple of days. It was then on to "lets get this thing gutted". I have to say the toy is well built watching all the stuffing getting pulled out. I gave it 3 stars because the toy is well built .The bear, pig, elephant, tug of war, mega ring, mega bone are all holding up nicely. Hadley the hammerhead lasted about a month before being gutted., My dog is a giant breed and a power chewer. He did get this ripped open and unstuffed on the first day, but he still has the unstuffed "carcass" and plays with it all the time. It's his favorite sleeping buddy. I gotta give it to lil Arnie, he's survived a lot longer than many of our other toys!, Started ripping apart after 30 minutes with my greyhounds., This toy is not tough enough for a Rottweiler or probably not for other big dogs, My dogs are not very destructive in general so I got them this toy. The youngest Kam really has fun with it. He is a Leonberger so having something substantial to carry is nice for him. He can shake it, run around with it, sticks it in the faces of the other dogs and keep running, has a blast with this toy. Thank you., Our goldendoodle loves soft toys but kills them instantly. This is our second armadillo. It's large size and "shell" help prolong it's life. She's had it a few weeks and we only have one tiny hole in the shell., Clyde is tough on all toys, so naturally I thought I would stick to all rubber toys or antlers never to find a plush toy that was durable enough to outlast a day in his clutches. He's always been able to chew through all so called "durable plushy toys" UNTIL TUFFYS CAME ALONG. reviews: [First, this bee was much larger than I realized it would be, that’s my fault for not reading the product details. We gave it to our 60 pound dog who is a toy chewer. Our dog loves to play with this toy and also sleeps with it on occasion. It is durable and holds up well to lots of toss and catch. He uses the wings to whip the toy around and toss it over his own head. Great toy!, I have a German Shepherd puppy that is relatively gentle with plush toys and with just one play session an eyeball was plucked off (Unsurprisingly since it was held by one thread connected at four points.) I hand sewed it back on and reenforced the other eye and they're holding better now. But he also tore a hole in the "reenforced fabric" which turned out to be one layer and a dozen tiny triangles of fabric sewn together instead of one large peice reenforced by stitching. He loved playing with it but the toy isn't so mighty. His Kong stuffed toy has lasted weeks with no damage. This one lasted an evening., My 45lb pit mix plucked all the legs off in a matter of minutes before taking off an eye. It's big, so there's more to chew off than with a smaller toy, but overall it was a big disappointment. I'm starting to think there are no plushies that will last more than a few minutes with my dog., Diego loves this! It’s well made. Very sturdy and thick.]

title: Fat Cat Water Bottle Crunchers Dog Toy, Color Varies
descriptions:
["Dogs just cant resist the satisfying crunch of an empty water bottle! That's why petmate designed Water Bottle Crunchers! Perfectly sized for empty water bottles (or any empty plastic bottle up to 20 oz in size!) This toy packs a punch with a crunch!", 'Ships in a variety of random and fun colors!', 'Every dog plays differently and, since not all toys are created equal, it’s always best to keep a close watch on your pup in case things get ruff. key_benefits: ['Made of heavy duty canvas for a fun sturdy toy', 'Entices dogs with a crunchy water bottle that can be taken out or refilled with a new one', 'Appeals to a dog’s natural instinct to  thrash and throw pray around', 'Floppy parts entice pups to play and chase', 'Great for a game of fetch or a comfort toy to cuddle with']
reviews: [What a great idea! However, the legs were immediately chewed off within 2 minutes of hard play. But, at least the bottle cover made the water bottle last longer than if there had not been a cover! My dog loves the sound of water bottle "crunching"., My dog was Not interested in this toy at all. I don’t for the life of me understand why but he just wouldn’t play with it!! Go figure! He loves his Chuck it football!!, Our 6mth old puppy tore this apart in 35 mins. She is a lab, border collie mix. She ripped it in 2 spots. Had to throw it away. Waste of money., My dog absolutely loves these bottle crunchers. She wore off her previous one. I ordered this toy because she likes to gnaw on cloth things. Was told that color varies - NO, what I got wasn't a cat with a bunch of paws to chew on. I received a snake with just head and tail. My dog could care less but it's the only reason this review doesn't get a 5. This is the only toy my dog loves to play tug of war with and loves the crunchy crunch sounds. I love that it came with a bottle already in it., I should have read more reviews. We also didn’t get the cat but got the snake. It came with a bottle which was nice, but the material is definitely not durable canvass. It’s more like thin nylon. This didn’t last 10 minutes., Thought I was getting a cat and got a random snake Again, not too long out of the box and my puppy chewed through the fabric on the corner where the Velcro is. Velcro area is kinda hard and stiff and stands out. First thing my puppy went for and within a half an hour, had a hole chewed through the corner of the Velcro. I guess I just need to be done with water bottle toys. I liked the concept and wanted it to work because my puppy likes them, but can’t find anything that holds up., The happy face of this Fat Cat and the crunchy water bottle body was certainly appealing to my 10 month old golden. However, her sneaky chewing style will find the weak point of almost every toy presented to her. This poor cat was killed in a matter of minute when my pup decided the velcro closure which looked quite secure, instead was the sweet weak spot. Gently chewing, she eventually tore the fabric and began to chew away the velcro. Alas, Fat Cat was rescued before more damage to both toy and pet could ensue., I love fat cat toys,they have always been sturdy and who can beat the graphics. Been buying them for 14 years now but as the hurl a squirrel , and Chuck a duck, that I also bought where made of the heavy duty canvas, this was not, My Newfoundland/poodle mix is absolutely obsessed with this. We got her a bunch of toys for her birthday and she picked this one up right away and was so excited! It seems like it’ll last for a while but she’s pretty gentle with her toys., Every dog is different and has different play styles so the toy might be destroyed a little quicker than most. I have an 8 month Malinois/Lab mix and when I brought this home, he loved it! Even when it was time to replace the water bottle, he was still throwing it in the air and having fun! And he didn't even break through the fabric which was a relief for me. Get it and try it out. Even if they destroy it immediately, at least they had fun!!]

title: Silly Squeakers Beer Bottles Squeaky Stuffing-Free Plush Dog Toy
descriptions:

key_benefits: ['Designed to suit dogs of all sizes, this hilarious toy makes an excellent gift for any pet lover.', 'Comparable in size to a typical 12-ounce beer bottle and designed for supervised play—scoring a 2 on Tuffy\'s "Tuff Scale," these bottles are not designed for chew time.', 'Includes 1 internal squeaker for a loud and rowdy house party.', 'Made of a custom blend of safe rubber that you can trust with your pooch.', "Tuffy's is known to make some of the world's most durable toys, so parents can be rest assured that, like a fine wine, this toy will only get better."]
reviews: [We got this squeaker to replace one just like it that was purchased at a different place of business. Literally after 2 minutes of my dog playing with it, the squeaker fell out. That’s the reason why we purchased another one is because our dog loves the loud squeaker. The previous toy that is identical to this one (it was purchased at a local store) never had this issue. Due to the pandemic we aren’t going into stores to limit exposure so that’s why we ordered this new one from Chewy. Pretty disappointed with this purchase., I wanted to love this for my 10 week old puppy. He loves playing w water bottles and thought this would be better. He broke it w/n one day and the plastic is easily chewed off. I expected more for the cost of this toy., I got this toy mostly to mess with my husband, but our great pyrenees 3 months old puppy seems to enjoy it quite a bit. Yeah, it can be loud if the dog gets excited about squeaky toys, best hide it if anyone in the household is still asleep. It is pretty good for fetch and easy to clean off the slobber. Our dog is not a destroyer, not sure if it would have survived the excitement of our previous dog (labrador)., My English Bulldog is OBSESSED with these! I bought one at a store once thinking he’d play with it occasionally. It ended up being his favorite toy! After a few months the squeaker quit, but he still takes it every where with him! I decided to buy him one in every color and was not disappointed. Overall, the toy is pretty durable, but the squeaker does not last very long. He doesn’t seem to mind though., Our mini-Goldendoodle chewed the cap of this bottle in less than 10 minutes. Guessing all the great reviews for this dog chew-toy came from the humans who like how it looks. Waste of money!, The squeaker already broke off and no longer makes a noise. I opened it 15 minutes ago and it’s already broken. Very expensive toy to already break., Cute, but my dog tore it to shreds within 10 minutes of playing with it. The description says they are known for the durability of their toys, but that doesn’t seem to be the case., This isn't as great as the tequila bottle (according to my dog) but I still think it's hilarious. Great toy for dogs who love a durable squeaky toy! Lucy is a bone mouth sharpei/boxer mix around 65-70 pounds., First toy we bought when we adopted our 3yr old husky and it is his absolute fave. Extremely durable with a loud squeaker that is indestructible. One of the only toys he hasn’t managed to demolish., I’ll start with the cons of this toy, because there aren’t many. The squeak is loud. So loud I had to hide this toy at night time lol. However the squeaker quit working after a few days. Could be the dog, could be something else. He still plays with it though. It’s made from a thicker rubbery material and he hasn’t punctured this toy whatsoever. He loves using it as a fetch toy as well.]

key_benefits: ['Strong, stuffing-free, noise-making toy', 'Features durable Rip Stop mesh lining for added strength', 'Reinforced with two layers for durability', 'No stuffing means endless amount of fun!', 'Can be stuffed with a plastic bottle for extra fun']
reviews: [Recently had a litter of pups and to help them from getting homesick... sent a Froggy home with each puppy (with the smell of their littermates) after the whole litter played with them for a couple weeks... and they held up great!!!!! and the new owners liked them too :) Did add the empty water bottles with caps and rings removed and the squeaky is not necessary to keep their attention., Of course, nothing lasts forever, but my little monsters have a blast ripping these toys to shreds. I end up de-stuffing the plush toys as soon as the seams are ripped anyway, so good on Skinneeez for being more eco-friendly. The empty Velcro pouch offers endless potential for reusing stuff around the house to make all kinds of satisfying noises for my boys. I’ve bought a few different styles from this brand and they’re all good quality., The squeaker stopped working in half a day. No puncture wounds, it just quit working, When I first gave the frog to my dogs they looked at it and reacted like "Ok another unstuffed toy!" Then I read the attached label and realized that you could insert an empty water bottle which made a crackling sound when they played with it. Now they can't get enough of it. My only issue is that I didn't buy one for each of them. Guess what is going on my next Chewy order!, My dog had this destroyed in about 15 minutes!!!! Took the speaker right out very cheaply made I even put a plastic bottle in it, I should have listened to the reviews I read before buying this. I think it is a splendid toy for a smaller dog but not for a larger and aggressive chewer like I have. It took all of about 10 minutes before my baby girl Siberian Husky had this in many pieces. Otherwise , a very nice toy., While my dog loved to play, and crunch on the plastic bottle placed inside.. the frogs nose was ripped open with the first hour., Was hopeful this toy would work for my pup. She loved the frog but it's not durable, so it same apart easily on first use. And the water bottle came out easily. Very disappointed., My dog loved the frog, unfortunately it did not last.i would say three days at most., My Welsh Terrier LOVES his frog! He squeaks it until he punctures all the squeakers and then carries it around like a trophy. I wish a pet toy maker would develop an indestructible squeaker! That would be awesome!!!]

reviews: [My 8 month old Golden Retriever has loved Skinneeez toys since I got him his first couple Mini Skinneeez toys when he was much younger. Even though the squeakers are broken on his mini's, he STILL loves them! So I knew I had to try these Extreme Skinneeez toys, he LOVES these as well! We now have two of each. He unfortunately broke one of the squeakers fairly quick on this toy, but the other squeaker is still working. The second Extreme has both squeakers in working condition. Sometimes he gets a tooth in just the right angle to bust a squeaker, but generally he doesn't try on purpose to break them, he loves making them squeak! The Skinneeez are his first choice of toy when I tell him to pick, My dog is a 35lb lab mix, about 1-2 years old. She was able to rip off the ears and paws quickly, and then I had to take away the toy because she had the tail open and I didn't want her to get the squeaker. It's great that there was no stuffing, but the toy was no tougher than an average stuffed animal. Would be good for a dog who doesn't wanted to chew their toy, This toy was larger than I expected for my 14 pound Bichon, but she loved it instantly and continued to for days after receiving it (which is very good for my toy-picky dog). There are two surdy squeakers in it which she loves to use to grab onto during tug, and she enjoys chewing the ears. This was definitely the best toy my 4-year-old pup has had in a long time., My Texas Heeler loves the idea of stuffed animals, but he usually chews on them until they fall apart or rips out the middle. We have had this toy for a month, and the only damage is a chewed off ear (each ear is smaller than a dime). The quilting seems to really strengthen the fabric. My dog does not play "tug of war" with this, but he carries it around, chews on it, and loves to hunt it. This is definitely a favorite toy and has stood up to lots of tough love!]

reviews: [GSD (60lbs; 2 years old) loves this toy! She has had it for about a month now and it still is hanging in there. She takes it with her to bed and brings it to me for play time. I’ve had my dog kill baby opossums before so trust when I say that instinct is already there. Your dog doesn’t know that opossums are extremely vulnerable and helpful to your yard. Makes a small sound so no loud squeaking and he loves it-so far still in one piece and it's been a week-that's a record-definitely recommend for a heavy chewer, My dog loved playing with this toy and the crinkle sound (and has had the same one before with no issues) but this one was stuffed with more cellophane than the others and she chewed through it in a week and the cellophane came out (which thankfully she didn’t eat after it came out) so keep an eye on your dog if she’s a chewer. Otherwise fun to play with., I bought 2 of these loofa toys for my puppies. They are a year old. They had the stuffing removed within the first 24 hours. I did notice, however, that it did promote shaking. They now carry around an empty loofa, Clooney is a Boston Terrier so I thought this hard to find crinkly toy was going to be too big (approximately the size of a saucer plate), however, Cloon dog has no problems shaking it until he is satisfied it's dead and he can start chewing on the ears. The material is soft and durable. All the ear chewing has done nothing. I have had to wash this toy a couple of times and it has lasted. No squeaker on this one. Will definitely order again., I have been looking for a crinkle toy without a squeaker inside and finally found it with this product! My goldendoodle is pretty rough on toys. She has had this for a week and it has totally held up. She brings it everywhere all around the house and even tries to sneak it outside. I will probably buy more of these., Our Yorkies love the crinkly sound,but the seams are not reinforced and our Yorkies were able to unravel them and pull out the cotton stuffing.Not safe unless under supervision., Very cute toy with crackle-noise interest, but not very durable for a chewer. Our GSD had the ears off within a day., Love this toy. Perfect for toy yorkie. There are no small pieces to chew off., This toy came up under a search for super chewers - it’s really cute but was destroyed in about 2 minutes]

title: ZippyPaws Warriorz Archibald the Archer Dog Toy
descriptions:
['Give your energetic dog the squeaking playtime fun he loves with the ZippyPaws Warriorz Archibald the Archer Dog Toy. This plush toy may be cute, but it’s also tough! It’s fortified from within with layers of dense fabrics, and thanks to its reinforced border webbing and sturdy stitching with exclusive Z-Stitch® Technology, it can hold up to some pretty serious play. With two large blaster squeakers inside and absolutely no stuffing, you can give your pal the loud, squeaking fun he loves, with none of the mess. Lightweight enough to be easily tossed for a quick game of fetch with your furry friend, it’s also ultra-cuddly for those more laid-back moments. It provides a stimulating and engaging activity for your dog to enjoy with you. Plus, pet parents everywhere will adore it as a special doggie gift.', 'Every dog plays differently and, since not all toys are created equal, it’s always best to keep a close watch on your pup in case things get ruff. Supervised play will help toys last longer and most importantly keep your pal safe. No dog toy is truly indestructible, so always remove the toy from playtime if pieces begin to break off.', '

                        See all items by ZippyPaws
']
key_benefits: ['Designed with dense fabrics to withstand tough play, so the fun can last longer.', 'Extra-durable with strong border webbing and tear-resistant, exclusive Z-Stitch® Technology.', 'Contains two loud blaster squeakers inside for the high squeakability your dog loves.', 'Stuffing-free for durable, anytime play, without any of the mess or hassle.', 'Great for dogs of all sizes and comes in different characters to match your pup’s personality.']
reviews: [I bought this because it looked like it didn’t have any “protruding” parts. If there are any noses, ears or parts that stick up, she rips them off and demolishes it. So this looked like it would be a contender and last more than 1 day, nope. It fell apart in just a few minutes. Back to the drawing board!, I purchased this over the weekend based on positive reviews from other "power chewer" and "aggressive chewer" owners. It lasted 7 minutes from the time we took it out of the chewy box. 7 whole minutes and money down the drain. Do not waste your money!, My Golden Retriever and German Shepherd love these! They last a really long time, and have several squeakies inside. Very loud and obnoxious! Total fun., My girl is infamous for chewing squeakers out of toys immediately. She hasn't been able to get through this one! She likes the super squeakers, but it's also great for tugging and for throwing for our lab., Mydog loves destroying toys, searching out the squeakers, and tearing apart the seams of toys, but so far this one has lasted really well! It is a very loud squeaker though!, We go through Kongs and Tuffies like water around here (normally our black lab mix is the culprit), but I picked up one of these in black at a local store without much expectation of it lasting but a couple of days. That was well over a month ago. It has NO holes or seam splitting AT ALL, and it is played with by our pups just like a tug-of-war toy. They love the squeakers (which still work) and we couldn't be more pleased with the durability. Great toy! We haven't even had to give them this green one yet, but we have great expectations of it :), The toy is much bigger than expected but it’s made very well and the squeaker is super loud which our dog loves., Love the look of this Warrior dog toy, but unfortunately my 10 lb puppy managed to chew through it within 15 minutes. He got the squeaker out and now not one of our three dogs are interested in it. Bummer!, My dog, Hamish, is a very aggressive chewer. For some reason he has decided not to destroy this toy. He loves the squeakers in it and with all the use, it still works. Squeakers eventually go after a lot of play but he still likes the doll and carries it around with him. So this is a winner for us. We now have three of them. And I will continue to buy them for him as it’s the only toy that he really likes. Thank you for making such a durable and adorable toy for my dog., I spent a while looking for a durable toy without any filling. My boy is a serious chewer and toys rarely last more than a couple days. This one has survived 3 weeks and still looks brand new! Fair warning, the squeakers are LOUD!]

reviews: [So, i bought this toy for my girl, Athena. She loves the toy and omg, she drove us nuts for a day squeaking the toy but, it broke in one day. But, even with the squeaker broken, she loves the toy. So, 4 stars is what I give it and highly recommend it., Bought this for my neighbors dog who was not feeling well . She loved it and seemed to feel better playing with it. After short time she chewed off the top of the wine bottle, making the toy squeekless. This dog "Keely" loves squeaky toys and takes very good care of them.She can destroy a stuffed animal in no time . Before I bought this I read a review on line that complained about the same problem and blamed it on poor construction. I think there is something about the top of the wine bottle that causes this to happen. The wine bottle is well constructed and made of steady material, the manufacturers should look into this., I know the product name saws plush, but what I received was like a rubber material. It was still hollow and soft, but it was not fabric material., My dog loves this thing and it kept her busy for quite some time, however, make sure you can handle the noise, lol! It's loud but I don't mind it. Not so good if you're on a conference call!, My dog loves this toy he have to play with it every day. He did break the squeaker with in a couple hours but he still love it., This a typical squeaking toy. I love the punny design, and my dog enjoys playing with it., My dog received a toy similar to this one, a tequila bottle. My dog is rough with toys and tears them apart. The other one lasted almost a year so I bought this one. My dog loves it! I am hoping it will last as long., Silicone material is so durable! My Boston terrier at first looked at this and walked away. About an hour later he can’t put it down. After about two weeks he was able to open it and destroy only the top. Still a great toy he picks up to play with. Squeak is loud, He really thinks he's "killing it" and can't believe no-one else wants to play! Be ready for lots of noise...sort of like giving your child a drum set., My cocker love love loves this toy! she is good about sharing but this one she won't put down! it is pretty large like the size of a tall glass beer bottle! the sqeak is so very loud! which drives my other dog nuts in jealousy! Have had it for a month and they just chewed the top off =/ for teething pup I will call that a win. I have told everyone I know about this toy though, the pix are worth the cost!!]

reviews: [This toy was great but only lasted a half day since there is fluff inside! I bought it from the no fluff tab and whazza it actually has fluff. It was delivered in a box that also had cat litter and they delivered it on the side instead of bottom and the cat litter had completely squished the toy, im not sure of that was a cause or not., This is cute but the grunting mechanism was broken when it arrived. reviews: [This is the perfect toy if you have a pet that loves to make their toys squeak! I have 3 shih tzu’s and 2/3 love their toys. This is big BUT it’s thin AND lightweight so even my 11lb dog can carry it around without a problem. Now I just need to remember to hide it in the late evening or she will start playing as we are getting ready for bed!, Our 2 year old German Shepherd loves this walrus toy! Since the stuffing is non-existent, I’m not chasing it down to clean up the stuffing before he eats it. He also loves the squeakers! It’s pretty solidly constructed. We’ve had it for a few weeks, and he’s managed to remove one flipper, but otherwise, it’s fully in tact., My pittie loves to tear up all things that are soft and have squeakers. Her goal is to get out each and every squeaker intact if possible! Because there are so many squeakers in this toy she would remove a few and then come back to it later so it lasted about 2 days (a lot by our standards). She had a great time with this toy and we will definitely be getting more for Christmas., This is great it still looks awesome with 5 dogs playing with it. It does squeak pretty loudly but they love it., My Great Dane had the tusks chewed off this toy in 30 seconds. The rest of the toy is holding up pretty well but the tusks need to either be made of something tougher or taken off altogether., We bought this, thinking it would last a while as the last set of three from chewy lasted our dog almost 6 months. It didnt even last an hour with our great Dane. Dont buy for big dogs., I will preface this by saying my dog is a big chewer, but she loves plush toys. We had ~some~ success with the alligator version of this toy, so I decided to get the walrus because it's so cute! She doesn't like toys specifically made for tough chewers - clearly the ability to destroy something is important to her! If you have a doggo that easily tears plush toys apart - move long!, I have a pittie mix who destroys everything within hours. This is like the 10th soft toy I've tried with her and this is the one. She has kongs, ropes, real and synthetic antlers, rubber chews, and this is her favorite toy of the bunch. She is right this moment carrying it around the house with her. By the 3rd day none of the sqeakers worked and she has gotten many of them out so this isnt a toy to be left unsupervised. But the multitude of broken squeakers make a rattle noise when shaken that she likes. He only has one arm now but other than that the stitching is surprisingly robust! Some of the face fluff came off and i had to take it away from her but again, as long as youre keeping an eye, Our 6 mo old cocker has fun dragging this light weight squeaker around. It has no filling and it is so light, she can take this everywhere she goes! A couple of the squeakers have stopped working but there's plenty more!, I keep trying to find a toy for my dog that will last. He loves the fabric toys, but none has survived for long. This was disappeared in about 1hr. My dog really enjoyed tearing it apart though.]

reviews: [I should I known, 15 minutes of glorious squeaking and our 9 month old boxer ( 50 lbs.) worked the inside squeaker out of the ball and is now working to take the cover off to find that small plastic part. Not for the aggressive types. Or the very busy ones ;), My Pointer mix loves this ball! Squeakers are his favorite but he has a habit of surgically removing them from toys in the first few minutes. Since there isn't one small squeaker to root around for the ball has had significant longevity over other toys. Be warned the squeak is more of a discordant screech but the dog loves it so I'll be smiling as my ears bleed. I also have a Mighty ring (how I was introduced to Mighty) and am ordering a Mighty bone. Tuffy and Kong have come and go but the Mighty is here to stay (as is my tinnitus)., This ball is a BALL to play with! Bigger than a softball, smaller than a basketball, so probably better for med to large dogs. We like this toy for indoor play. When the weather isn't cooperating, we can roll this big, fun ball down the hall and our dog will do this thousands of times and never get bored. The outside is a soft fleece that has held up extremely well to how much we play. The ball itself is a giant squeak-ball, so also fun to squeak and throw for added excitement. We love this big MIGHTY ball!, First I love mighty brand toys as they last and are fairly safe for dogs . ( I pick up when they are done playing ) . But my healer girl loves this ball , so of corse I do also., Somehow, I have no idea how, he managed to get the squeaker out of the ball without ripping the material. Its literally moving around between the ball and the material. He's the Herry Houdini of squeaky killing. Just got it today and within an hour, he killed it. Within the first few minutes the ball would collapse and slowly inflate back up. Right where my finger is is where the squeaker piece isn't longer in the ball. Hes not even chewing the ball hes just playing with it. Hes a total nut ball. I thought it might work because the ball is bigger than his head., only made it for 2 play sessions. We definitely had fun kicking it for the first session. By session number 2 there was a hole in it and completely torn apart, Love it. The sound is great when you mush it down Can grab it when it’s flattened down and run around with it as it expands, Diogi had a ball like this before, but it was smaller, probably 4 inches. He loves this big ball and can get his huge mouth around it to make it squeak! Sister Honey, AKA Destructor of Toys, can’t get her mouth around it to tear it up. I hear it squeaking several times a day. Now, it IS big, so it isn’t suitable for smaller dogs. Diogi is a 83 pound boxer/something-very-big mix., I have an large Aussie puppy (75 pounds) who is a chewer. This ball entertains him (he loves to make it squeak), and so far, it's holding up very well to him chasing and grabbing it with his teeth. It's a heavy ball, with a harder surface under the tough cloth, which probably makes it more durable. Glad I bought this one!, My dog loves these balls. I’ve had three. He inevitably tears them apart as he does all toys. They are a nemesis to be destroyed. But they last as long as any with him. He’s so ridiculously happy with these. Why? It is very easy to bite and it is very very easy to squeak. The squeaking will drive you crazy. But his face and obvious enchantment with this overrides that. I guess I was obnoxious as a kid as well. Buy it.]

reviews: [My 65lb black lab loves this toy. He really doesn’t destroy his toys. He squeaks them until they can no longer squeak. He loves this one., Annie was very excited to get her new toy, as she always is. She loved the new Mighty dog bone. I had hoped it would last awhile based on the toy’s description since Annie usually loves her toys into oblivion pretty quickly. Literally, within ten minutes she had chewed through the flannel-type covering and then it only took a few minutes more to get through the plastic of the bone itself. The toy might be fine for a big dog who isn’t a destroyer, but unfortunately was no match for Annie., I have an 80lb Airedale and he loves this toy! The squeakers last a good long while, and the rubber bone has stayed in tact loonnnnnggggg after the felt covering has been torn off., Our dog cannot get enough of his Mighty Ball so we thought we would give the Mighty Bone a go! He loves this toy! It is soft and fuzzy on the outside, and the inside bone shape is a whole squeaker toy, so we run all over the house squeaking it and playing endlessly. We keep this toy and others put up when we are away, so it does help the toys last longer. Would highly recommend the Mighty Bone!, I got this toy for my 1 year old German Shepherd. She has destroyed every plush toy I bought from Chewy within days. I bought this toy thinking it would be more durable, but the entire first layer was ripped off in 3 days and now she won't play with it., Our dog is no longer able to have soft or squeaky toys even though he loves them. He rips them to shreds in minutes. Not this one, completely intact after 10 play periods. Really excellent product. Our dog is a heavy chewer. We do put it away after play time., This is the longest time my 25 lb super chewer has ever had one toy that has remained relatively intact. He ripped the outer plush covering to reveal the rubber inside and the squeaker no longer works; however he continues to play with this rubber today everyday! No holes or rips in the rubber. I will buy another one for him to have an extra. I recommend to anyone with shredding chewers!, Our teen age GSD likes this toy pretty well - it's not a favorite, but he plays with it regularly, and hasn't damaged it at all with his amazingly sharp teeth., I got this toy for my puppies and they did play with it for awhile but then got bored as puppies will. So I gave it my adult Boxers and they l loved it! One of my Boxers is known as the "Toy Destructor" and she hasn't been able to "kill" this one yet or get the squeaker out (yet-time will tell-but so far so good and it's been a couple of weeks!), Our 8 month old golden retriever is ruthless with his toys. Most of the labeled "extra strong" toys take at maximum 2 days to have ripped to shreds. This one has lasted almost 3 week! A big win in our families shoes!]

reviews: [My Corgi pup is obsessed with these doughnuts. They are indeed, as described in a previous review, not plush, but instead two plastic halves with squeakers. This has not deterred my Corgi from loving these doughnuts. He fetches them, catches them, chases them, and squeaks them. One of the six did tear over time, but the other 5 are still in great shape, even after multiple runs through the washer on delicate. I will be ordering another box of these, so my pup won’t be without his favorite doughnuts., The description states: "Super-soft with a fun squeaker" and "Features poly-fill for a plush experience." That is NOT TRUE. I purchased a poly-filled doughnut toy LOCALLY and, based on the description and photo, thought that these would be the same thing -- they were not. These toys CONTAIN NO STUFFING! They are basically two half round STIFF SQUEAKERS covered in fabric, so we have to be careful tossing them around in the house. Based on their stiffness, I don't think that very small dogs would be able to get them to squeak. I don't like them, and would not purchase again. On the plus side, our hound dog loves anything that makes noise, and they DO have multiple squeaky sounds in each doughnut, Our 45# Portuguese Water Dog loves these squeaky throw toys. His first choice was the chocolate. I wash everything. These toys stay together and continue to squeak after going through a cycle. Our 5# terrier mix granddaughter can live without it. I think the donut is not a good fit for her mouth.]

reviews: [I ordered this toy because it was on sale. I bought the extra large beaver super squeaker and my lab loves it, so I thought that the large racoon would be the same.
